<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Opuntia</i> <i>littoralis</i> and/or other cacti are dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Cleome</i> <i>isomeris</i>, <i>Cneoridium</i> <i>dumosum</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>prolifera</i>, <i>Encelia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Euphorbia</i> <i>misera</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i>, <i>Lycium</i> spp., <i>Malosma</i> <i>laurina</i>, <i>Mirabilis</i> <i>laevis</i> var. <i>crassifolia</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> ×<i>occidentalis</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>oricola</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> <i>phaeacantha</i>, <i>Opuntia</i> ×<i>vaseyi</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i> and <i>Sambucus</i> <i>nigra</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Schinus</i> <i>molle</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy intermittent or continuous in two tiers. Herbaceous layer is open to continuous and diverse. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Opuntia littoralis</i> and/or other cacti (such as <i>Cylindropuntia prolifera</i> and <i>O. oricola</i>) are > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006).</li>
		
		<li><i>Opuntia littoralis</i> is > 30% relative cover as a dominant or co-dominant with other coastal sage scrub species (Evens and San 2005, Klein and Evens 2005).</li>
		
		<li><i>Opuntia littoralis, Cylindropuntia prolifera</i> and/or <i>O. oricola</i>) are > 30% relative cover in the shrub layer, or may be as low as 20% relative cover if the absolute cover is more than one-third that of the dominant coastal scrub species (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> South-facing slopes, headlands. Soils are shallow, loams and clays that may be rocky.  </div>
</div>

        
